          <mi>A</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mo>…</mo>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>A</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>m</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle \\;A_{1},\\ldots ,A_{m}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/da7e13ed42437deca4d0727c624626e0e10a25fa\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:12.039ex; height:2.509ex;\" alt=\"\\;A_{1},\\ldots ,A_{m}\"></span> is <b>fully <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\displaystyle \\;m}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mspace width=\"thickmathspace\"></mspace>\n        <mi>m</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle \\;m}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d3c27e2965725e567b805b0c591a875ee5622f8b\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.686ex; height:1.676ex;\" alt=\"\\;m\"></span>-partite separable</b> if and only if it can be written\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\displaystyle \\;|\\Psi _{A_{1}\\ldots A_{m}}\\rangle =|\\psi _{A_{1}}\\rangle \\otimes \\ldots \\otimes |\\psi _{A_{m}}\\rangle .}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mspace width=\"thickmathspace\"></mspace>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">?</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>A</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n            <mo>…</mo>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>A</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mi>m</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo fence=\"false\" stretchy=\"false\">?</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>?</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>A</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo fence=\"false\" stretchy=\"false\">?</mo>\n        <mo>?</mo>\n        <mo>…</mo>\n        <mo>?</mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>?</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>A</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mi>m</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo fence=\"false\" stretchy=\"false\">?</mo>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle \\;|\\Psi _{A_{1}\\ldots A_{m}}\\rangle =|\\psi _{A_{1}}\\rangle \\otimes \\ldots \\otimes |\\psi _{A_{m}}\\rangle .}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/21708f458c130ac57e3ca400b9486f86c961714c\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:34.17ex; height:3.009ex;\" alt=\"\\;|\\Psi _{{A_{1}\\ldots A_{m}}}\\rangle =|\\psi _{{A_{1}}}\\rangle \\otimes \\ldots \\otimes |\\psi _{{A_{m}}}\\rangle .\"></span><sup id=\"cite_ref-quantiki_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multipartite_entanglement#cite_note-quantiki-1\">[1]</a></sup></dd></dl>\n<p>In order to check this, it is enough to compute reduced density \nmatrices of elementary subsystems and see whether they are pure. \nHowever, this cannot be done so easily in the multipartite case, as only\n rarely multipartite pure states admit the <i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Bipartite_states_and_Schmidt_Decomposition&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Bipartite states and Schmidt Decomposition (page does not exist)\">generalized Schmidt Decomposition</a></i> <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\displaystyle \\;|\\Psi _{A_{1}\\ldots A_{m}}\\rangle =\\sum _{i=1}^{min\\{d_{A_{1}},\\ldots ,d_{A_{m}}\\}}a_{i}|e_{A_{1}}^{i}\\rangle \\otimes \\ldots \\otimes |e_{A_{m}}^{i}\\rangle }\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mspace width=\"thickmathspace\"></mspace>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">?</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>A</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n            <mo>…</mo>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>A</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mi>m</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo fence=\"false\" stretchy=\"false\">?</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <munderover>\n          <mo>?</mo>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n            <mo>=</mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>m</mi>\n            <mi>i</mi>\n            <mi>n</mi>\n            <mo fence=\"false\" stretchy=\"false\">{</mo>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>d</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <msub>\n                  <mi>A</mi>\n                  <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                    <mn>1</mn>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msub>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n            <mo>,</mo>\n            <mo>…</mo>\n            <mo>,</mo>\n            <msub>\n              <mi>d</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <msub>\n                  <mi>A</mi>\n                  <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                    <mi>m</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msub>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n            <mo fence=\"false\" stretchy=\"false\">}</mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </munderover>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <msubsup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>A</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msubsup>\n        <mo fence=\"false\" stretchy=\"false\">?</mo>\n        <mo>?</mo>\n        <mo>…</mo>\n        <mo>?</mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mo stretchy=\"false\">|</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <msubsup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <msub>\n              <mi>A</mi>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mi>m</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msub>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msubsup>\n        <mo fence=\"false\" stretchy=\"false\">?</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle \\;|\\Psi \n_{A_{1}\\ldots A_{m}}\\rangle =\\sum _{i=1}^{min\\{d_{A_{1}},\\ldots \n,d_{A_{m}}\\}}a_{i}|e_{A_{1}}^{i}\\rangle \\otimes \\ldots \\otimes \n|e_{A_{m}}^{i}\\rangle }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/fb0ef0be00f76ad9f94ef56fc8c413b63bf465b6\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -3.005ex; width:48.706ex; height:8.009ex;\" alt=\"\\;|\\Psi _{{A_{1}\\ldots A_{m}}}\\rangle =\\sum _{{i=1}}^{{min\\{d_{{A_{1}}},\\ldots ,d_{{A_{m}}}\\}}}a_{i}|e_{{A_{1}}}^{i}\\rangle \\otimes \\ldots \\otimes |e_{{A_{m}}}^{i}\\rangle \"></span>.\n A multipartite state admits generalized Schmidt decomposition if, \ntracing out any subsystem, the rest is in a fully separable state. \nThus, in general the entanglement of a pure state is described by the \nspectra of the reduced density matrices of all bipartite partitions: the\n state is <b>genuinely <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\displaystyle \\;m}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mspace width=\"thickmathspace\"></mspace>\n        <mi>m</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle \\;m}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d3c27e2965725e567b805b0c591a875ee5622f8b\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.686ex; height:1.676ex;\" alt=\"\\;m\"></span>-partite entangled</b> if and only if all bipartite partitions produce mixed reduced density matrices.<sup id=\"cite_ref-quantiki_1-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multipartite_entanglement#cite_note-quantiki-1\">[1]</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Mixed_states\">Mixed states</span></h3><p>In the multipartite case there is no simple necessary and sufficient condition for separability like the one given by the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peres%E2%80%93Horodecki_criterion\" title=\"Peres–Horodecki criterion\">PPT criterion</a> for the <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\displaystyle 2\\otimes 2}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mn>2</mn>\n        <mo>?</mo>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle 2\\otimes 2}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/6c85f419d3d66d4007cad69d397336a0a749fa2c\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.505ex; width:5.165ex; height:2.343ex;\" alt=\"2\\otimes 2\"></span> and <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\displaystyle 2\\otimes 3}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mn>2</mn>\n        <mo>?</mo>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle 2\\otimes 3}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d6600be817f32311dd974a3d507eb41fc32fb19d\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -0.505ex; width:5.165ex; height:2.343ex;\" alt=\"2\\otimes 3\"></span> cases. However, many <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Separability_criteria&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Separability criteria (page does not exist)\">separability criteria</a> used in the bipartite setting can be generalized to the multipartite case.<sup id=\"cite_ref-quantiki_1-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multipartite_entanglement#cite_note-quantiki-1\">[1]</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h4><span id=\"Positive_but_not_completely_positive_.28PnCP.29_maps_and_entanglement_witnesses\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Positive_but_not_completely_positive_(PnCP)_maps_and_entanglement_witnesses\">Positive but not completely positive (PnCP) maps and entanglement witnesses</span></h4><p>The characterization of separability in terms of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Separability_criteria&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Separability criteria (page does not exist)\">positive but not completely positive maps</a> can be naturally generalized from the bipartite case, as follows.<sup id=\"cite_ref-quantiki_1-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multipartite_entanglement#cite